ul.li:
x-z	Letter x should be z. Symbols x and z represent any letter that stands for a consonant.
            Example: {æfinnar}${con,stem,f-v|ævinnar}; {pragt}${con,stem,g-k|prakt}; {Viktaðar}${con,stem,k-g|Vigtaðar};
               {huxast}${con,stem,x-gs|hugsast}

com	Consonant omission. Closely tied to phonology. The middle consonant in a consonant
            cluster is not represented in pronounciation and so the writing represents the pronounciation,
            with the middle consonant missing. Can also apply to one of two adjacent consonants.
            Example: {fræsluna}${con,stem,com|fræðsluna}; {sjálboðaliða}${con,stem,com|sjálfboðaliða};
               {stærfræðikennara}${con,stem,com|stærðfræðikennara}; {stærfræðikennaranum}${con,stem,com|stærðfræðikennaranum};
               {únliðnum}${con,stem,com|úlnliðnum}; {víðfemt}${con,stem,com|víðfeðmt}; {þarnast}${con,stem,com|þarfnast}
